article.headline: Kent State 70, Shawnee State 47
article.story: KENT, Ohio (AP) -- Omni Smith scored 13 points to lead Kent State to a 70-47 win over Shawnee State in the second game of the Kent State Classic on Friday night. Kent (6-5) outrebounded Shawnee State 35-27 and took advantage of the Bears' miscues, scoring 20 points off of 24 Shawnee State turnovers. Shawnee State's only lead came in the opening minutes of the game when the Bears (9-5) took a 4-2 lead on Aaron Davis' 3-pointer with 17:43 left in the half. Josh Reed had 12 points and five rebounds for the Bears. The Golden Flashes' scored seven quick points to open the second half and take their largest lead of the game at 49-21 with 16:56 left to play. The Bears would not get within 22 points for the remainder of the game. Mike McKee scored 11 points and Mike Scott added 10 for Kent.
